<P class=3Dparagraph>Your task is to graph the price of a stock over =
time. In one=20
unit of time, the stock can either <B>R</B>ise, <B>F</B>all or stay=20
<B>C</B>onstant. The stock's price will be given to you as a string of =
R's, F's=20
and C's. You need to graph it using the characters '/' (slash), '\' =
(backslash)=20
and '_' (underscore). </P>
<P class=3Dparagraph><FONT size=3D5><B>Input</B></FONT><BR>The first =
line of input=20
gives the number of cases, <B>N</B>. <B>N</B> test cases follow. Each =
one=20
contains a string of at least 1 and at most 50 upper case characters (R, =
F or=20
C). </P>
<P class=3Dparagraph><FONT size=3D5><B>Output</B></FONT><BR>For each =
test case,=20
output the line "Case #<B>x</B>:", where <B>x</B> is the number of the =
test=20
case. Then print the graph, as shown in the sample output, including the =
x- and=20
y-axes. The x-axis should be one character longer than the graph, and =
there=20
should be one space between the y-axis and the start of the graph. There =
should=20
be no trailing spaces on any line. Do not print unnecessary lines. The =
x-axis=20
should always appear directly below the graph. Finally, print an empty =
line=20
after each test case. </P>
